SUMMARY:How to Write about the World
DESCRIPTION:The weirder the world gets\, the more it lends itself to journalism; particularly journalism that runs long\, in the form of narrative features or books.  \nThis panel discussion brings together Samanth Subramanian\, author of The Web Beneath the Waves\, and the veteran journalists Aakar Patel and Sharda Ugra\, to spend the evening talking shop. They discuss approaches to stories\, narrate anecdotes of interviews gone right (and wrong!)\, recall misbegotten reporting trips\, bemoan the state of narrative journalism today\, and relish the genuine thrill of being a journalist out in the field. \nGlobal reportage redefined through Indian eyes. \n\n\nThe Craft of Journalism in Our Strange and Complex Times\nRSVP here (https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdslvgqTKhyEtjN_P8-tLoqNzc9kSXScDPI_4qhA_SCL9Nprw/viewform?usp=pp_url)\n*Speakers*: Samanth Subramanian\, Sharda Ugra\, Aakar Patel\n*Event Categories*: Books\, Media\, Nonfiction\, Society
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/how-to-write-about-the-world/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Books,Media,Nonfiction,Society
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Thumbnail_Jy-13.jpg
END:VEVENT
