SUMMARY:Science X Community: Reimagining Urban Lakes
DESCRIPTION:For decades\, Bengaluru’s citizens\, institutions\, and experts have worked tirelessly to save the city’s lakes. Marking a step in that effort\, the Framework for Lake Rejuvenation is being launched. The comprehensive\, five-step document\, co-created by Friends of Lakes and WELL Labs along with Greater Bengaluru Authority\, citizen groups\, NGOs\, academics\, and experts\, addresses the need to capture collective knowledge in a common\, transparent\, and streamlined framework to guide future lake rejuvenation efforts across the city. \nThe launch will be followed by a panel discussion that brings together a diverse group of voices\, from citizen lake groups to researchers\, practitioners\, and environmental advocates\, to answer a simple question: how can Bengaluru move toward a scientifically grounded\, long-term strategy that ensures lakes remain healthy and functional for generations? \nThis event aims to spark a conversation about how the city can move from isolated projects to a shared\, science-based approach for rejuvenating and sustaining its lakes. \nPresented by: \n \n\n\nBuilding a Shared Lake Rejuvenation Framework for Resilient Cities\nRSVP here (https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd0zRqP6iHLcdYrrd-5JOCdQeo-HtmC0h9dnM4g6Qb-JJx6Tw/viewform?usp=pp_url)\n*Speakers*: Anupama Shetty\, V Ramprasad\, Avinash Krishnamurthy\, Sujata C Hingorani\, Veena Srinivasan\n*Event Categories*: Bangalore\, Environment\, Governance\, Policy & Regulation\, Public Health\, Society\, Sustainability
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/science-x-community-reimagining-urban-lakes/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Bangalore,Environment,Governance,Policy & Regulation,Public Health,Society,Sustainability
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Thumbnail_SxC_RUL.jpg
